August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Top-seeded Sachia Vickery beat second-seeded Alexandra Kiick 4-6, 6-2, 6-0 on Sunday to win the USTA Girls' 18s National Championship at Barnes Tennis Center. Read story

Donovan has hat trick, Galaxy, FC Dallas draw 3-3

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

FRISCO, Texas (AP) -- Landon Donovan scored three goals for his fourth career MLS hat trick, but Blas Perez scored his second goal in the 86th minute to lift FC Dallas into a 3-3 tie with the Los Angeles Galaxy on Sunday night. Read story

Steinhauer wins on Legends Tour

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

JACKSON, Mich. (AP) -- Sherri Steinhauer won a playoff Sunday in the Legends Tour's Wendy's Charity Challenge, beating Christa Johnson on the second extra hole. Read story

Kevin Durant returns to Seattle in summer league

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

SEATTLE (AP) -- Kevin Durant hoisted 62 shots and scored 63 points, played all but 15 seconds in 51 minutes of game time. Read story

Katy Harris wins Symetra Tour event

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

PALM HARBOR, Fla. (AP) -- Katy Harris won the IOA Golf Classic on Sunday for her first Symetra Tour title, finishing with a 3-under 69 for a one-stroke victory over Alejandra Llaneza. Read story

Liberty upend Dream 88-82

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

ATLANTA (AP) -- Cappie Pondexter scored 33 points and the New York Liberty earned an 88-82 victory over the Atlanta Dream on Sunday. Read story

Raiders rookie Sio Moore impresses early

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

NAPA, Calif. (AP) -- At 6-foot-1, 240 pounds, Oakland rookie linebacker Sio Moore is far from an ideal matchup to put his hand down and rush against a 300-plus pound NFL offensive tackle. Read story

Sky slip past Lynx in OT 94-86

August 10, 2013, 5:00pm Imported

ROSEMONT, Ill. (AP) -- Elena Delle Donne forced overtime with a clutch 3-pointer and had a career-high 32 points to lead the Chicago Sky to a 94-86 victory over Minnesota on Sunday. Read story
